## Description {#details}

Represents a JIT&#39;d dynamic library.

This class aims to mimic the behavior of a regular dylib or shared object, but without requiring the contained program representations to be compiled up-front. The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>&#39;s content is defined by adding MaterializationUnits, and contained MaterializationUnits will typically rely on the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>&#39;s links-against order to resolve external references (similar to a regular dylib).

The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> object is a thin wrapper that references state held by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a>. JITDylibs can be removed, clearing this underlying state and leaving the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> object in a defunct state. In this state the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>&#39;s name is guaranteed to remain accessible. If the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a> is still alive then other operations are callable but will return an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> or null result (depending on the API). It is illegal to call any operation other than getName on a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> after the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a> has been torn down.

JITDylibs cannot be moved or copied. Their address is stable, and useful as a key in some JIT data structures.

### addGenerator() {#ae89dfebe97fc65907c1b9194aafe1ade}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename GeneratorT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>GeneratorT &amp; llvm::orc::JITDylib::addGenerator (std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; GeneratorT &gt; DefGenerator)</>}>
Adds a definition generator to this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> and returns a referenece to it.

When JITDylibs are searched during lookup, if no existing definition of a symbol is found, then any generators that have been added are run (in the order that they were added) to potentially generate a definition.

It is illegal to call this method on a defunct <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> and the client is responsible for ensuring that they do not do so.

### clear() {#a25e558db9c4a9a9b6cbd5dc09a2b929b}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="Error llvm::orc::JITDylib::clear ()">
Calls remove on all trackers currently associated with this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

Does not run static deinits.

Note that removal happens outside the session lock, so new code may be added concurrently while the clear is underway, and the newly added code will <em>not</em> be cleared. Adding new code concurrently with a clear is usually a bug and should be avoided.

It is illegal to call this method on a defunct <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> and the client is responsible for ensuring that they do not do so.

### remove() {#a22901ece72bc281bb4690fad971c4eb5}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::orc::JITDylib::remove (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#ada98b2ca88b7bc4b65b62e3269fdade7">SymbolNameSet</a> &amp; Names)</>}>
Tries to remove the given symbols.

If any symbols are not defined in this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> this method will return a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolsnotfound">SymbolsNotFound</a> error covering the missing symbols.

If all symbols are found but some symbols are in the process of being materialized this method will return a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolscouldnotberemoved">SymbolsCouldNotBeRemoved</a> error.

On success, all symbols are removed. On failure, the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> state is left unmodified (no symbols are removed).

It is illegal to call this method on a defunct <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> and the client is responsible for ensuring that they do not do so.

### setLinkOrder() {#ab5c917be01faae33e9df9295e1dffdd7}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::orc::JITDylib::setLinkOrder (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a1a2b573da544cf233d62075a16146245">JITDylibSearchOrder</a> NewSearchOrder, bool LinkAgainstThisJITDylibFirst=<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/basicaliasanalysis-cpp/#af6d5cafbdfc5313e65d990120021a3ec">true</a>)</>}>
Set the link order to be used when fixing up definitions in <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

This will replace the previous link order, and apply to any symbol resolutions made for definitions in this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> after the call to setLinkOrder (even if the definition itself was added before the call).

If LinkAgainstThisJITDylibFirst is true (the default) then this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> will add itself to the beginning of the LinkOrder (Clients should not put this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> in the list in this case, to avoid redundant lookups).

If LinkAgainstThisJITDylibFirst is false then the link order will be used as-is. The primary motivation for this feature is to support deliberate shadowing of symbols in this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> by a facade <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>. For example, the facade may resolve function names to stubs, and the stubs may compile lazily by looking up symbols in this dylib. Adding the facade dylib as the first in the link order (instead of this dylib) ensures that definitions within this dylib resolve to the lazy-compiling stubs, rather than immediately materializing the definitions in this dylib.

It is illegal to call this method on a defunct <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> and the client is responsible for ensuring that they do not do so.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h/#l00989">989</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h">Core.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp/#l01004">1004</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp">Core.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

## Public Static Functions

### getDFSLinkOrder() {#a814ccfa400b06db7a01885ddcc21196a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::vector&lt; JITDylibSP &gt; &gt; llvm::orc::JITDylib::getDFSLinkOrder (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a1baadbec01aced37be13a1b86c76397e">JITDylibSP</a> &gt; JDs)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Returns the given JITDylibs and all of their transitive dependencies in DFS order (based on linkage relationships).

Each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> will appear only once.

If any <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> in the order is defunct then this method will return an error, otherwise returns the order.

### getReverseDFSLinkOrder() {#a095093bca58ff168e74cfa75cebf3865}

<MemberDefinition

Returns the given JITDylibs and all of their transitive dependencies in reverse DFS order (based on linkage relationships).

Each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> will appear only once.

If any <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> in the order is defunct then this method will return an error, otherwise returns the order.
